President Muhammadu Buhari Wednesday met privately with the Speaker of the House of Representatives, Honourable Femi Gbajabiamila to discuss issues bordering on the state of the nation.  Addressing State House Correspondent after the meeting at the Presidential Villa Abuja, the Speaker said the issue of herders/farmers unhealthy relationship in the south west and the south East will be addressed by the House upon resumption next week, adding that no ethnic group should Lord over another in Nigeria.  Our Correspondent, Raliat Adenekan reports that while speaking on the newly appointed service chiefs, the Speaker assured that the National Assembly would give them all the necessary support.Â Honourable Gbajabiamila urged all party members, youths, new party members who have attained 18years of age to participate in the ongoing registration and revalidation of All Progressives Congress membership